64 // Provides JavaScript-specific "macro-assembler" functionality on top of the
65 // CodeAssembler. By factoring the JavaScript-isms out of the CodeAssembler,
66 // it's possible to add JavaScript-specific useful CodeAssembler "macros"
67 // without modifying files in the compiler directory (and requiring a review
68 // from a compiler directory OWNER).
69 class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE CodeStubAssembler
70  : public compiler::CodeAssembler,
71  public TorqueGeneratedExportedMacrosAssembler {
72  public:
73  using ScopedExceptionHandler = compiler::ScopedExceptionHandler;
74

76  using LazyNode = std::function<TNode<T>()>;

78  explicit CodeStubAssembler(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state);

112  bool ToParameterConstant(TNode<Smi> node, intptr_t* out) {
113  if (TryToIntPtrConstant(node, out)) {
114  return true;
115  }
116  return false;
117  }
118 
119  bool ToParameterConstant(TNode<IntPtrT> node, intptr_t* out) {
120  intptr_t constant;
121  if (TryToIntPtrConstant(node, &constant)) {
122  *out = constant;
123  return true;
124  }
125  return false;
126  }

224 #define PARAMETER_BINOP(OpName, IntPtrOpName, SmiOpName) \
225  TNode<Smi> OpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { return SmiOpName(a, b); } \
226  TNode<IntPtrT> OpName(TNode<IntPtrT> a, TNode<IntPtrT> b) { \
227  return IntPtrOpName(a, b); \
228  } \
229  TNode<UintPtrT> OpName(TNode<UintPtrT> a, TNode<UintPtrT> b) { \
230  return Unsigned(IntPtrOpName(Signed(a), Signed(b))); \
231  } \
232  TNode<RawPtrT> OpName(TNode<RawPtrT> a, TNode<RawPtrT> b) { \
233  return ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(IntPtrOpName( \
234  ReinterpretCast<IntPtrT>(a), ReinterpretCast<IntPtrT>(b))); \
235  }
236  // TODO(v8:9708): Define BInt operations once all uses are ported.
237  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiAdd, IntPtrAdd, SmiAdd)
238  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiSub, IntPtrSub, SmiSub)
239 #undef PARAMETER_BINOP
240 
241 #define PARAMETER_BINOP(OpName, IntPtrOpName, SmiOpName) \
242  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { return SmiOpName(a, b); } \
243  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<IntPtrT> a, TNode<IntPtrT> b) { \
244  return IntPtrOpName(a, b); \
245  } \
246  /* IntPtrXXX comparisons shouldn't be used with unsigned types, use */ \
247  /* UintPtrXXX operations explicitly instead. */ \
248  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<UintPtrT> a, TNode<UintPtrT> b) { UNREACHABLE(); } \
249  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<RawPtrT> a, TNode<RawPtrT> b) { UNREACHABLE(); }
250  // TODO(v8:9708): Define BInt operations once all uses are ported.
251  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiEqual, WordEqual, SmiEqual)
252  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiNotEqual, WordNotEqual, SmiNotEqual)
253  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiLessThan, IntPtrLessThan, SmiLessThan)
254  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiLessThanOrEqual, IntPtrLessThanOrEqual,
255  SmiLessThanOrEqual)
256  PARAMETER_BINOP(IntPtrOrSmiGreaterThan, IntPtrGreaterThan, SmiGreaterThan)
257 #undef PARAMETER_BINOP
258 
259 #define PARAMETER_BINOP(OpName, UintPtrOpName, SmiOpName) \
260  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { return SmiOpName(a, b); } \
261  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<IntPtrT> a, TNode<IntPtrT> b) { \
262  return UintPtrOpName(Unsigned(a), Unsigned(b)); \
263  } \
264  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<UintPtrT> a, TNode<UintPtrT> b) { \
265  return UintPtrOpName(a, b); \
266  } \
267  TNode<BoolT> OpName(TNode<RawPtrT> a, TNode<RawPtrT> b) { \
268  return UintPtrOpName(a, b); \
269  }
270  // TODO(v8:9708): Define BInt operations once all uses are ported.
271  PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiEqual, WordEqual, SmiEqual)
272  PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiNotEqual, WordNotEqual, SmiNotEqual)
273  PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiLessThan, UintPtrLessThan, SmiBelow)
274  PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiLessThanOrEqual, UintPtrLessThanOrEqual,
275  SmiBelowOrEqual)
276  PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiGreaterThan, UintPtrGreaterThan, SmiAbove)
277  PARAMETER_BINOP(UintPtrOrSmiGreaterThanOrEqual, UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual,
278  SmiAboveOrEqual)
279 #undef PARAMETER_BINOP

281  uintptr_t ConstexprUintPtrShl(uintptr_t a, int32_t b) { return a << b; }
282  uintptr_t ConstexprUintPtrShr(uintptr_t a, int32_t b) { return a >> b; }
283  intptr_t ConstexprIntPtrAdd(intptr_t a, intptr_t b) { return a + b; }
284  uintptr_t ConstexprUintPtrAdd(uintptr_t a, uintptr_t b) { return a + b; }
285  intptr_t ConstexprWordNot(intptr_t a) { return ~a; }
286  uintptr_t ConstexprWordNot(uintptr_t a) { return ~a; }

288 #if defined(V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE) || defined(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX)
289  void CheckObjectComparisonAllowed(TNode<AnyTaggedT> a, TNode<AnyTaggedT> b,
290  SourceLocation loc);
291 #endif
292 
293  TNode<BoolT> TaggedEqual(TNode<AnyTaggedT> a, TNode<AnyTaggedT> b,
294  SourceLocation loc = SourceLocation::Current()) {
295 #if defined(V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE) || defined(V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX)
296  if (v8_flags.enable_slow_asserts) {
297  CheckObjectComparisonAllowed(a, b, loc);
298  }
299 #endif
300  if (COMPRESS_POINTERS_BOOL) {
301  return Word32Equal(ReinterpretCast<Word32T>(a),
302  ReinterpretCast<Word32T>(b));
303  } else {
304  return WordEqual(ReinterpretCast<WordT>(a), ReinterpretCast<WordT>(b));
305  }
306  }
307 
308  TNode<BoolT> TaggedNotEqual(TNode<AnyTaggedT> a, TNode<AnyTaggedT> b,
309  SourceLocation loc = SourceLocation::Current()) {
310  return Word32BinaryNot(TaggedEqual(a, b, loc));
311  }
312 
313  // A variant of TaggedEqual which allows comparing objects in different
314  // pointer compression cages. In particular, this should be used when
315  // comparing objects in trusted- or code space with objects in the main
316  // pointer compression cage. Currently only defined for HeapObject, this
317  // type can be expanded if needed.
318  TNode<BoolT> SafeEqual(TNode<HeapObject> a, TNode<HeapObject> b) {
319  if (V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE_BOOL || V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL) {
320  return WordEqual(BitcastTaggedToWord(a), BitcastTaggedToWord(b));
321  }
322  return TaggedEqual(a, b);
323  }
324 
325  TNode<BoolT> SafeNotEqual(TNode<HeapObject> a, TNode<HeapObject> b) {
326  return Word32BinaryNot(SafeEqual(a, b));
327  }

331  TNode<IntPtrT> StackAlignmentInBytes() {
332  // This node makes the graph platform-specific. To make sure that the graph
333  // structure is still platform independent, UniqueIntPtrConstants are used
334  // here.
335 #if V8_TARGET_ARCH_ARM64
336  return UniqueIntPtrConstant(16);
337 #else
338  return UniqueIntPtrConstant(kSystemPointerSize);
339 #endif
340  }

423  // Smi operations.
424 #define SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiOpName, IntPtrOpName, Int32OpName) \
425  TNode<Smi> SmiOpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { \
426  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) { \
427  return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned( \
428  IntPtrOpName(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), \
429  BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b))); \
430  } else { \
431  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits()); \
432  return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Int32OpName( \
433  TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)), \
434  TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b))))); \
435  } \
436  }
437  SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiAdd, IntPtrAdd, Int32Add)
438  SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiSub, IntPtrSub, Int32Sub)
439  SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiAnd, WordAnd, Word32And)
440  SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiOr, WordOr, Word32Or)
441  SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP(SmiXor, WordXor, Word32Xor)
442 #undef SMI_ARITHMETIC_BINOP

460  TNode<Smi> UnsignedSmiShl(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
461  if (SmiValuesAre32Bits()) {
462  return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(
463  WordShl(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), shift));
464  } else {
465  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits());
466  return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Word32Shl(
467  TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)),
468  Int32Constant(shift))));
469  }
470  }
471 
472  TNode<Smi> SmiShl(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
473  TNode<Smi> result = UnsignedSmiShl(a, shift);
474  // Smi shift have different result to int32 shift when the inputs are not
475  // strictly limited. The CSA_DCHECK is to ensure valid inputs.
476  CSA_DCHECK(
477  this, TaggedEqual(result, BitwiseOp(SmiToInt32(a), Int32Constant(shift),
478  Operation::kShiftLeft)));
479  return result;
480  }
481 
482  TNode<Smi> SmiShr(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
483  TNode<Smi> result;
484  if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) {
485  result = BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(
486  WordAnd(WordShr(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), shift),
487  BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
488  } else {
489  // For pointer compressed Smis, we want to make sure that we truncate to
490  // int32 before shifting, to avoid the values of the top 32-bits from
491  // leaking into the sign bit of the smi.
492  result = BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(WordAnd(
493  ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Word32Shr(
494  TruncateWordToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)),
495  shift)),
496  BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
497  }
498  // Smi shift have different result to int32 shift when the inputs are not
499  // strictly limited. The CSA_DCHECK is to ensure valid inputs.
500  CSA_DCHECK(
501  this, TaggedEqual(result, BitwiseOp(SmiToInt32(a), Int32Constant(shift),
502  Operation::kShiftRightLogical)));
503  return result;
504  }
505 
506  TNode<Smi> SmiSar(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) {
507  // The number of shift bits is |shift % 64| for 64-bits value and |shift %
508  // 32| for 32-bits value. The DCHECK is to ensure valid inputs.
509  DCHECK_LT(shift, 32);
510  if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) {
511  return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(
512  WordAnd(WordSar(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), shift),
513  BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
514  } else {
515  // For pointer compressed Smis, we want to make sure that we truncate to
516  // int32 before shifting, to avoid the values of the top 32-bits from
517  // changing the sign bit of the smi.
518  return BitcastWordToTaggedSigned(WordAnd(
519  ChangeInt32ToIntPtr(Word32Sar(
520  TruncateWordToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)),
521  shift)),
522  BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(SmiConstant(-1))));
523  }
524  }
525 
526  TNode<Smi> WordOrSmiShr(TNode<Smi> a, int shift) { return SmiShr(a, shift); }
527 
528  TNode<IntPtrT> WordOrSmiShr(TNode<IntPtrT> a, int shift) {
529  return WordShr(a, shift);
530  }
531 
532 #define SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiOpName, IntPtrOpName, Int32OpName) \
533  TNode<BoolT> SmiOpName(TNode<Smi> a, TNode<Smi> b) { \
534  if (kTaggedSize == kInt64Size) { \
535  return IntPtrOpName(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a), \
536  BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b)); \
537  } else { \
538  DCHECK_EQ(kTaggedSize, kInt32Size); \
539  DCHECK(SmiValuesAre31Bits()); \
540  return Int32OpName( \
541  TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(a)), \
542  TruncateIntPtrToInt32(BitcastTaggedToWordForTagAndSmiBits(b))); \
543  } \
544  }
545  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiEqual, WordEqual, Word32Equal)
546  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiNotEqual, WordNotEqual, Word32NotEqual)
547  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiAbove, UintPtrGreaterThan, Uint32GreaterThan)
548  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiAboveOrEqual, UintPtrGreaterThanOrEqual,
549  Uint32GreaterThanOrEqual)
550  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiBelow, UintPtrLessThan, Uint32LessThan)
551  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiBelowOrEqual, UintPtrLessThanOrEqual,
552  Uint32LessThanOrEqual)
553  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiLessThan, IntPtrLessThan, Int32LessThan)
554  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiLessThanOrEqual, IntPtrLessThanOrEqual,
555  Int32LessThanOrEqual)
556  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiGreaterThan, IntPtrGreaterThan, Int32GreaterThan)
557  SMI_COMPARISON_OP(SmiGreaterThanOrEqual, IntPtrGreaterThanOrEqual,
558  Int32GreaterThanOrEqual)
559 #undef SMI_COMPARISON_OP

738  template <typename T>
739  TNode<T> Select(TNode<BoolT> condition, const NodeGenerator<T>& true_body,
740  const NodeGenerator<T>& false_body,
741  BranchHint branch_hint = BranchHint::kNone) {
742  TVARIABLE(T, value);
743  Label vtrue(this), vfalse(this), end(this);
744  Branch(condition, &vtrue, &vfalse, branch_hint);
745 
746  BIND(&vtrue);
747  {
748  value = true_body();
749  Goto(&end);
750  }
751  BIND(&vfalse);
752  {
753  value = false_body();
754  Goto(&end);
755  }
756 
757  BIND(&end);
758  return value.value();
759  }
760 
761  template <class A>
762  TNode<A> SelectConstant(TNode<BoolT> condition, TNode<A> true_value,
763  TNode<A> false_value) {
764  return Select<A>(
765  condition, [=] { return true_value; }, [=] { return false_value; });
766  }

818  // Check if lower_limit <= value <= higher_limit.
819  template <typename U>
820  TNode<BoolT> IsInRange(TNode<Word32T> value, U lower_limit, U higher_limit) {
821  DCHECK_LE(lower_limit, higher_limit);
822  static_assert(sizeof(U) <= kInt32Size);
823  if (lower_limit == 0) {
824  return Uint32LessThanOrEqual(value, Int32Constant(higher_limit));
825  }
826  return Uint32LessThanOrEqual(Int32Sub(value, Int32Constant(lower_limit)),
827  Int32Constant(higher_limit - lower_limit));
828  }
829 
830  TNode<BoolT> IsInRange(TNode<UintPtrT> value, TNode<UintPtrT> lower_limit,
831  TNode<UintPtrT> higher_limit) {
832  CSA_DCHECK(this, UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(lower_limit, higher_limit));
833  return UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(UintPtrSub(value, lower_limit),
834  UintPtrSub(higher_limit, lower_limit));
835  }
836 
837  TNode<BoolT> IsInRange(TNode<WordT> value, intptr_t lower_limit,
838  intptr_t higher_limit) {
839  DCHECK_LE(lower_limit, higher_limit);
840  if (lower_limit == 0) {
841  return UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(value, IntPtrConstant(higher_limit));
842  }
843  return UintPtrLessThanOrEqual(IntPtrSub(value, IntPtrConstant(lower_limit)),
844  IntPtrConstant(higher_limit - lower_limit));
845  }

1181  template <class Type>
1182  void StoreRawArgument(uint32_t index, TNode<Type> value) {
1183  DCHECK_LT(index, IsolateData::GetRawArgumentCount());

1188 
1189  // Load a field from an object on the heap.
1190  template <typename T>
1191  TNode<T> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset) {
1192  MachineType machine_type = MachineTypeOf<T>::value;
1193  TNode<IntPtrT> raw_offset = IntPtrConstant(offset - kHeapObjectTag);
1194  if constexpr (is_subtype_v<T, UntaggedT>) {
1195  // Load an untagged field.
1196  return UncheckedCast<T>(LoadFromObject(machine_type, object, raw_offset));
1197  } else {
1198  static_assert(is_subtype_v<T, Object>);
1199  // Load a tagged field.
1200  if constexpr (is_subtype_v<T, Map>) {
1201  // If this is potentially loading a map, we need to check the offset.
1202  if (offset == HeapObject::kMapOffset) {
1203  machine_type = MachineType::MapInHeader();
1204  }
1205  }
1206  return CAST(LoadFromObject(machine_type, object, raw_offset));
1207  }
1208  }
1209  TNode<Object> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset) {
1210  return UncheckedCast<Object>(
1211  LoadFromObject(MachineType::AnyTagged(), object,
1212  IntPtrConstant(offset - kHeapObjectTag)));
1213  }
1214  TNode<Object> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1215  TNode<IntPtrT> offset) {
1216  return UncheckedCast<Object>(
1217  LoadFromObject(MachineType::AnyTagged(), object,
1218  IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
1219  }
1220  template <class T>
1221  TNode<T> LoadObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object, TNode<IntPtrT> offset)
1222  requires std::is_convertible_v<TNode<T>, TNode<UntaggedT>>
1223  {
1224  return UncheckedCast<T>(
1225  LoadFromObject(MachineTypeOf<T>::value, object,
1226  IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
1227  }
1228  // Load a positive SMI field and untag it.
1229  TNode<IntPtrT> LoadAndUntagPositiveSmiObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1230  int offset);
1231  // Load a SMI field, untag it, and convert to Word32.
1232  TNode<Int32T> LoadAndUntagToWord32ObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1233  int offset);
1234 
1235  TNode<MaybeObject> LoadMaybeWeakObjectField(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1236  int offset) {
1237  return UncheckedCast<MaybeObject>(LoadObjectField(object, offset));
1238  }

1248 
1249  // Reference is the CSA-equivalent of a Torque reference value, representing
1250  // an inner pointer into a HeapObject.
1251  //
1252  // The object can be a HeapObject or an all-zero bitpattern. The latter is
1253  // used for off-heap data, in which case the offset holds the actual address
1254  // and the data must be untagged (i.e. accessed via the Load-/StoreReference
1255  // overloads for TNode<UntaggedT>-convertible types below).
1256  //
1257  // TODO(gsps): Remove in favor of flattened {Load,Store}Reference interface.
1258  struct Reference {
1259  TNode<Object> object;
1260  TNode<IntPtrT> offset;
1261 
1262  std::tuple<TNode<Object>, TNode<IntPtrT>> Flatten() const {
1263  return std::make_tuple(object, offset);
1264  }
1265  };
1266 
1267  template <class T>
1268  TNode<T> LoadReference(Reference reference)
1269  requires std::is_convertible_v<TNode<T>, TNode<Object>>
1270  {
1271  if (IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset)) {
1272  TNode<Map> map = LoadMap(CAST(reference.object));
1273  DCHECK((std::is_base_of_v<T, Map>));
1274  return ReinterpretCast<T>(map);
1275  }
1276 
1277  TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1278  IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1279  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(reference.object));
1280  return CAST(
1281  LoadFromObject(MachineTypeOf<T>::value, reference.object, offset));
1282  }
1283  template <class T>
1284  TNode<T> LoadReference(Reference reference)
1285  requires(std::is_convertible_v<TNode<T>, TNode<UntaggedT>> ||
1286  is_maybe_weak_v<T>)
1287  {
1288  DCHECK(!IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset));
1289  TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1290  IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1291  return UncheckedCast<T>(
1292  LoadFromObject(MachineTypeOf<T>::value, reference.object, offset));
1293  }
1294  template <class T>
1295  void StoreReference(Reference reference, TNode<T> value)
1296  requires(std::is_convertible_v<TNode<T>, TNode<MaybeObject>>)
1297  {
1298  if (IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset)) {
1299  DCHECK((std::is_base_of_v<T, Map>));
1300  return StoreMap(CAST(reference.object), ReinterpretCast<Map>(value));
1301  }
1302  MachineRepresentation rep = MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value;
1303  StoreToObjectWriteBarrier write_barrier = StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kFull;
1304  if (std::is_same_v<T, Smi>) {
1305  write_barrier = StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kNone;
1306  } else if (std::is_same_v<T, Map>) {
1307  write_barrier = StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kMap;
1308  }
1309  TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1310  IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1311  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedIsNotSmi(reference.object));
1312  StoreToObject(rep, reference.object, offset, value, write_barrier);
1313  }
1314  template <class T>
1315  void StoreReference(Reference reference, TNode<T> value)
1316  requires std::is_convertible_v<TNode<T>, TNode<UntaggedT>>
1317  {
1318  DCHECK(!IsMapOffsetConstant(reference.offset));
1319  TNode<IntPtrT> offset =
1320  IntPtrSub(reference.offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag));
1321  StoreToObject(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value, reference.object, offset,
1322  value, StoreToObjectWriteBarrier::kNone);
1323  }
1324 
1325  TNode<RawPtrT> GCUnsafeReferenceToRawPtr(TNode<Object> object,
1326  TNode<IntPtrT> offset) {
1327  return ReinterpretCast<RawPtrT>(
1328  IntPtrAdd(BitcastTaggedToWord(object),
1329  IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag))));
1330  }

1747  // Store to an indirect pointer field. This involves loading the index for
1748  // the pointer table entry owned by the pointed-to object (which points back
1749  // to it) and storing that into the specified field.

1751  // pointer tag for the field. Otherwise, it is not needed

1753  IndirectPointerTag tag,
1754  TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);

1757  TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);

1761  // pointer table. Otherwise they are regular tagged fields.
1762  void StoreTrustedPointerField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1763  IndirectPointerTag tag,
1764  TNode<ExposedTrustedObject> value);

1771  // Store a code pointer field.
1772  // These are special versions of trusted pointers that, when the sandbox is
1773  // enabled, reference code objects through the code pointer table.
1774  void StoreCodePointerField(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1775  TNode<Code> value) {
1776  StoreTrustedPointerField(object, offset, kCodeIndirectPointerTag, value);
1777  }
1778  void StoreCodePointerFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1779  TNode<Code> value) {
1780  StoreTrustedPointerFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset,
1781  kCodeIndirectPointerTag, value);
1782  }

1784  template <class T>
1785  void StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object,
1786  TNode<IntPtrT> offset, TNode<T> value) {
1787  int const_offset;
1788  if (TryToInt32Constant(offset, &const_offset)) {
1789  return StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier<T>(object, const_offset, value);
1790  }
1791  StoreNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value, object,
1792  IntPtrSub(offset, IntPtrConstant(kHeapObjectTag)),
1793  value);
1794  }
1795  template <class T>
1796  void StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(TNode<HeapObject> object, int offset,
1797  TNode<T> value) {
1798  if (CanBeTaggedPointer(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value)) {
1799  OptimizedStoreFieldAssertNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value,
1800  object, offset, value);
1801  } else {
1802  OptimizedStoreFieldUnsafeNoWriteBarrier(MachineRepresentationOf<T>::value,
1803  object, offset, value);
1804  }
1805  }

1808  int offset, TNode<Object> value);

1835  template <typename TIndex>
1836  void StoreFixedArrayElement(
1837  TNode<FixedArray> array, TNode<TIndex> index, TNode<Object> value,
1838  WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER,
1839  int additional_offset = 0,
1840  CheckBounds check_bounds = CheckBounds::kAlways) {
1841  // TODO(v8:9708): Do we want to keep both IntPtrT and UintPtrT variants?
1842  static_assert(std::is_same_v<TIndex, Smi> ||
1843  std::is_same_v<TIndex, UintPtrT> ||
1844  std::is_same_v<TIndex, IntPtrT>,
1845  "Only Smi, UintPtrT or IntPtrT index is allowed");
1846  if (NeedsBoundsCheck(check_bounds)) {
1847  FixedArrayBoundsCheck(array, index, additional_offset);
1848  }
1849  StoreFixedArrayOrPropertyArrayElement(array, index, value, barrier_mode,
1850  additional_offset);
1851  }
1852 
1853  template <typename TIndex>
1854  void StoreFixedArrayElement(TNode<FixedArray> array, TNode<TIndex> index,
1855  TNode<Smi> value, int additional_offset = 0) {
1856  static_assert(
1857  std::is_same_v<TIndex, Smi> || std::is_same_v<TIndex, IntPtrT>,
1858  "Only Smi or IntPtrT indeces is allowed");
1859  StoreFixedArrayElement(array, index, TNode<Object>{value},
1860  UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER, additional_offset);
1861  }

1863  // These don't emit a bounds-check. As part of the security-performance
1864  // tradeoff, only use it if it is performance critical.
1865  void UnsafeStoreFixedArrayElement(
1866  TNode<FixedArray> object, int index, TNode<Object> value,
1867  WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1868  return StoreFixedArrayElement(object, IntPtrConstant(index), value,
1869  barrier_mode, 0, CheckBounds::kDebugOnly);
1870  }
1871  template <typename Array>
1872  void UnsafeStoreArrayElement(
1873  TNode<Array> object, int index,
1874  TNode<typename Array::Shape::ElementT> value,
1875  WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1876  DCHECK(barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER ||
1877  barrier_mode == UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER ||
1878  barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1879  // TODO(jgruber): This is just a barebones implementation taken from
1880  // StoreFixedArrayOrPropertyArrayElement. We can make it more robust and
1881  // generic if needed.
1882  int offset = Array::OffsetOfElementAt(index);
1883  if (barrier_mode == UNSAFE_SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1884  UnsafeStoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset, value);
1885  } else if (barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1886  StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset, value);
1887  } else if (barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1888  StoreObjectField(object, offset, value);
1889  } else {
1890  UNREACHABLE();
1891  }
1892  }
1893  template <typename Array>
1894  void UnsafeStoreArrayElement(
1895  TNode<Array> object, TNode<Smi> index,
1896  TNode<typename Array::Shape::ElementT> value,
1897  WriteBarrierMode barrier_mode = UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1898  DCHECK(barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER ||
1899  barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER);
1900  // TODO(jgruber): This is just a barebones implementation taken from
1901  // StoreFixedArrayOrPropertyArrayElement. We can make it more robust and
1902  // generic if needed.
1903  TNode<IntPtrT> offset = ElementOffsetFromIndex(index, PACKED_ELEMENTS,
1904  OFFSET_OF_DATA_START(Array));
1905  if (barrier_mode == SKIP_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1906  StoreObjectFieldNoWriteBarrier(object, offset, value);
1907  } else if (barrier_mode == UPDATE_WRITE_BARRIER) {
1908  StoreObjectField(object, offset, value);
1909  } else {
1910  UNREACHABLE();
1911  }
1912  }
1913

2171  enum class HoleConversionMode { kDontConvert, kConvertToUndefined };
2172  // Clone a fast JSArray |array| into a new fast JSArray.

2439  enum class ExtractFixedArrayFlag {
2440  kFixedArrays = 1,
2441  kFixedDoubleArrays = 2,
2442  kDontCopyCOW = 4,
2443  kAllFixedArrays = kFixedArrays | kFixedDoubleArrays,
2444  kAllFixedArraysDontCopyCOW = kAllFixedArrays | kDontCopyCOW
2445  };
2446 
2447  using ExtractFixedArrayFlags = base::Flags<ExtractFixedArrayFlag>;
2448 
2449  // Copy a portion of an existing FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray into a new
2450  // array, including special appropriate handling for empty arrays and COW
2451  // arrays. The result array will be of the same type as the original array.
2452  //
2453  // * |source| is either a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray from which to copy
2454  // elements.
2455  // * |first| is the starting element index to copy from, if nullptr is passed
2456  // then index zero is used by default.
2457  // * |count| is the number of elements to copy out of the source array
2458  // starting from and including the element indexed by |start|. If |count| is
2459  // nullptr, then all of the elements from |start| to the end of |source| are
2460  // copied.
2461  // * |capacity| determines the size of the allocated result array, with
2462  // |capacity| >= |count|. If |capacity| is nullptr, then |count| is used as
2463  // the destination array's capacity.
2464  // * |extract_flags| determines whether FixedArrays, FixedDoubleArrays or both
2465  // are detected and copied. Although it's always correct to pass
2466  // kAllFixedArrays, the generated code is more compact and efficient if the
2467  // caller can specify whether only FixedArrays or FixedDoubleArrays will be
2468  // passed as the |source| parameter.
2469  // * |parameter_mode| determines the parameter mode of |first|, |count| and
2470  // |capacity|.
2471  // * If |var_holes_converted| is given, any holes will be converted to
2472  // undefined and the variable will be set according to whether or not there
2473  // were any hole.
2474  // * If |source_elements_kind| is given, the function will try to use the
2475  // runtime elements kind of source to make copy faster. More specifically, it
2476  // can skip write barriers.
2477  template <typename TIndex>
2478  TNode<FixedArrayBase> ExtractFixedArray(
2479  TNode<FixedArrayBase> source, std::optional<TNode<TIndex>> first,
2480  std::optional<TNode<TIndex>> count = std::nullopt,
2481  std::optional<TNode<TIndex>> capacity = std::nullopt,
2482  ExtractFixedArrayFlags extract_flags =
2483  ExtractFixedArrayFlag::kAllFixedArrays,
2484  TVariable<BoolT>* var_holes_converted = nullptr,
2485  std::optional<TNode<Int32T>> source_elements_kind = std::nullopt);
2486 
2487  // Copy a portion of an existing FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray into a new
2488  // FixedArray, including special appropriate handling for COW arrays.
2489  // * |source| is either a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray from which to copy
2490  // elements. |source| is assumed to be non-empty.
2491  // * |first| is the starting element index to copy from.
2492  // * |count| is the number of elements to copy out of the source array
2493  // starting from and including the element indexed by |start|.
2494  // * |capacity| determines the size of the allocated result array, with
2495  // |capacity| >= |count|.
2496  // * |source_map| is the map of the |source|.
2497  // * |from_kind| is the elements kind that is consistent with |source| being
2498  // a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray. This function only cares about double vs.
2499  // non-double, so as to distinguish FixedDoubleArray vs. FixedArray. It does
2500  // not care about holeyness. For example, when |source| is a FixedArray,
2501  // PACKED/HOLEY_ELEMENTS can be used, but not PACKED_DOUBLE_ELEMENTS.
2502  // * |allocation_flags| and |extract_flags| influence how the target
2503  // FixedArray is allocated.
2504  // * |convert_holes| is used to signify that the target array should use
2505  // undefined in places of holes.
2506  // * If |convert_holes| is true and |var_holes_converted| not nullptr, then
2507  // |var_holes_converted| is used to signal whether any holes were found and
2508  // converted. The caller should use this information to decide which map is
2509  // compatible with the result array. For example, if the input was of
2510  // HOLEY_SMI_ELEMENTS kind, and a conversion took place, the result will be
2511  // compatible only with HOLEY_ELEMENTS and PACKED_ELEMENTS.
2512  template <typename TIndex>
2513  TNode<FixedArray> ExtractToFixedArray(
2514  TNode<FixedArrayBase> source, TNode<TIndex> first, TNode<TIndex> count,
2515  TNode<TIndex> capacity, TNode<Map> source_map, ElementsKind from_kind,
2516  AllocationFlags allocation_flags, ExtractFixedArrayFlags extract_flags,
2517  HoleConversionMode convert_holes,
2518  TVariable<BoolT>* var_holes_converted = nullptr,
2519  std::optional<TNode<Int32T>> source_runtime_kind = std::nullopt);
2520 
2521  // Attempt to copy a FixedDoubleArray to another FixedDoubleArray. In the case
2522  // where the source array has a hole, produce a FixedArray instead where holes
2523  // are replaced with undefined.
2524  // * |source| is a FixedDoubleArray from which to copy elements.
2525  // * |first| is the starting element index to copy from.
2526  // * |count| is the number of elements to copy out of the source array
2527  // starting from and including the element indexed by |start|.
2528  // * |capacity| determines the size of the allocated result array, with
2529  // |capacity| >= |count|.
2530  // * |source_map| is the map of |source|. It will be used as the map of the
2531  // target array if the target can stay a FixedDoubleArray. Otherwise if the
2532  // target array needs to be a FixedArray, the FixedArrayMap will be used.
2533  // * |var_holes_converted| is used to signal whether a FixedArray
2534  // is produced or not.
2535  // * |allocation_flags| and |extract_flags| influence how the target array is
2536  // allocated.
2537  template <typename TIndex>
2538  TNode<FixedArrayBase> ExtractFixedDoubleArrayFillingHoles(
2539  TNode<FixedArrayBase> source, TNode<TIndex> first, TNode<TIndex> count,
2540  TNode<TIndex> capacity, TNode<Map> source_map,
2541  TVariable<BoolT>* var_holes_converted, AllocationFlags allocation_flags,
2542  ExtractFixedArrayFlags extract_flags);
2543 
2544  // Copy the entire contents of a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray to a new
2545  // array, including special appropriate handling for empty arrays and COW
2546  // arrays.
2547  //
2548  // * |source| is either a FixedArray or FixedDoubleArray from which to copy
2549  // elements.
2550  // * |extract_flags| determines whether FixedArrays, FixedDoubleArrays or both
2551  // are detected and copied. Although it's always correct to pass
2552  // kAllFixedArrays, the generated code is more compact and efficient if the
2553  // caller can specify whether only FixedArrays or FixedDoubleArrays will be
2554  // passed as the |source| parameter.
2555  TNode<FixedArrayBase> CloneFixedArray(
2556  TNode<FixedArrayBase> source,
2557  ExtractFixedArrayFlags flags =
2558  ExtractFixedArrayFlag::kAllFixedArraysDontCopyCOW);
2559

2563  // |to_kind| elements.
2564  template <typename TResult>
2565  TNode<TResult> LoadElementAndPrepareForStore(TNode<FixedArrayBase> array,
2566  TNode<IntPtrT> offset,
2567  ElementsKind from_kind,
2568  ElementsKind to_kind,

3237  // Returns true if the bit field |BitField| in |word32| is equal to a given
3238  // constant |value|. Avoids a shift compared to using DecodeWord32.
3239  template <typename BitField>
3240  TNode<BoolT> IsEqualInWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32,
3241  typename BitField::FieldType value) {
3242  TNode<Word32T> masked_word32 =
3243  Word32And(word32, Int32Constant(BitField::kMask));
3244  return Word32Equal(masked_word32, Int32Constant(BitField::encode(value)));
3245  }
3246 
3247  // Checks if two values of non-overlapping bitfields are both set.
3248  template <typename BitField1, typename BitField2>
3249  TNode<BoolT> IsBothEqualInWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32,
3250  typename BitField1::FieldType value1,
3251  typename BitField2::FieldType value2) {
3252  static_assert((BitField1::kMask & BitField2::kMask) == 0);
3253  TNode<Word32T> combined_masked_word32 =
3254  Word32And(word32, Int32Constant(BitField1::kMask | BitField2::kMask));
3255  TNode<Int32T> combined_value =
3256  Int32Constant(BitField1::encode(value1) | BitField2::encode(value2));
3257  return Word32Equal(combined_masked_word32, combined_value);
3258  }
3259 
3260  // Returns true if the bit field |BitField| in |word32| is not equal to a
3261  // given constant |value|. Avoids a shift compared to using DecodeWord32.
3262  template <typename BitField>
3263  TNode<BoolT> IsNotEqualInWord32(TNode<Word32T> word32,
3264  typename BitField::FieldType value) {
3265  return Word32BinaryNot(IsEqualInWord32<BitField>(word32, value));
3266  }

3542  // Operating mode for TryGetOwnProperty and CallGetterIfAccessor
3543  enum GetOwnPropertyMode {
3544  // kCallJSGetterDontUseCachedName is used when we want to get the result of
3545  // the getter call, and don't use cached_name_property when the getter is
3546  // the function template and it has cached_property_name, which would just
3547  // bailout for the IC system to create a named property handler
3548  kCallJSGetterDontUseCachedName,
3549  // kCallJSGetterUseCachedName is used when we want to get the result of
3550  // the getter call, and use cached_name_property when the getter is
3551  // the function template and it has cached_property_name, which would call
3552  // GetProperty rather than bailout for Generic/NoFeedback load
3553  kCallJSGetterUseCachedName,
3554  // kReturnAccessorPair is used when we're only getting the property
3555  // descriptor
3556  kReturnAccessorPair
3557  };
3558  // Receiver handling mode for TryGetOwnProperty and CallGetterIfAccessor.

3562  kExpectingJSReceiver,
3563  // The receiver can be anything, it has to be converted to JSReceiver
3564  // in case a function callback template has to be called.
3565  kExpectingAnyReceiver,
3566  };

3658  // Generic property lookup generator. If the {object} is fast and
3659  // {unique_name} property is found then the control goes to {if_found_fast}
3660  // label and {var_meta_storage} and {var_name_index} will contain
3661  // DescriptorArray and an index of the descriptor's name respectively.
3662  // If the {object} is slow or global then the control goes to {if_found_dict}
3663  // or {if_found_global} and the {var_meta_storage} and {var_name_index} will
3664  // contain a dictionary and an index of the key field of the found entry.
3665  // If property is not found or given lookup is not supported then
3666  // the control goes to {if_not_found} or {if_bailout} respectively.
3667  //
3668  // Note: this code does not check if the global dictionary points to deleted
3669  // entry! This has to be done by the caller.

3676  Label* if_not_found, Label* if_bailout);

4064  void GotoIfStringEqual(TNode<String> lhs, TNode<IntPtrT> lhs_length,
4065  TNode<String> rhs, Label* if_true) {
4066  Label if_false(this);
4067  // Callers must handle the case where {lhs} and {rhs} refer to the same
4068  // String object.
4069  CSA_DCHECK(this, TaggedNotEqual(lhs, rhs));
4070  TNode<IntPtrT> rhs_length = LoadStringLengthAsWord(rhs);
4071  BranchIfStringEqual(lhs, lhs_length, rhs, rhs_length, if_true, &if_false,
4072  nullptr);
4073 
4074  BIND(&if_false);
4075  }
4076

4078  Label* if_false,
4079  TVariable<Boolean>* result = nullptr) {
4080  return BranchIfStringEqual(lhs, LoadStringLengthAsWord(lhs), rhs,
4081  LoadStringLengthAsWord(rhs), if_true, if_false,
4082  result);
4083  }

4235  // Indicate that this code must support a dynamic parameter count.
4236  //
4237  // This is used for builtins that must work on functions with different
4238  // parameter counts. In that case, the true JS parameter count is only known
4239  // at runtime and must be obtained in order to compute the total number of
4240  // arguments (which may include padding arguments). The parameter count is
4241  // subsequently available through the corresponding CodeAssembler accessors.
4242  // The target function object and the dispatch handle need to be passed in
4243  // and are used to obtain the actual parameter count of the called function.
4244  //
4245  // This should generally be invoked directly at the start of the function.
4246  //
4247  // TODO(saelo): it would be a bit nicer if this would happen automatically in
4248  // the function prologue for functions marked as requiring this (e.g. via the
4249  // call descriptor). It's not clear if that's worth the effort though for the
4250  // handful of builtins that need this.
4251  void SetSupportsDynamicParameterCount(
4252  TNode<JSFunction> callee, TNode<JSDispatchHandleT> dispatch_handle);
4253 
4254  // Figure out the SFI's code object using its data field.
4255  // If |data_type_out| is provided, the instance type of the function data will
4256  // be stored in it. In case the code object is a builtin (data is a Smi),
4257  // data_type_out will be set to 0.
4258  // If |if_compile_lazy| is provided then the execution will go to the given
4259  // label in case of an CompileLazy code object.
4260  TNode<Code> GetSharedFunctionInfoCode(
4261  TNode<SharedFunctionInfo> shared_info,
4262  TVariable<Uint16T>* data_type_out = nullptr,
4263  Label* if_compile_lazy = nullptr);

4440  // CSA does not support 64-bit types on 32-bit platforms so as a workaround
4441  // the kMaxSafeIntegerUint64 is defined as uintptr and allowed to be used only
4442  // inside if constexpr (Is64()) i.e. on 64-bit architectures.
4443  static uintptr_t MaxSafeIntegerUintPtr() {
4444 #if defined(V8_HOST_ARCH_64_BIT)
4445  // This ifdef is required to avoid build issues on 32-bit MSVC which
4446  // complains about static_cast<uintptr_t>(kMaxSafeIntegerUint64).
4447  return kMaxSafeIntegerUint64;
4448 #else
4449  UNREACHABLE();
4450 #endif
4451  }

4665  TNode<BoolT> IsPageFlagSet(TNode<IntPtrT> object, int mask) {
4666  TNode<IntPtrT> header = MemoryChunkFromAddress(object);
4667  TNode<IntPtrT> flags = UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(
4668  Load(MachineType::Pointer(), header,
4669  IntPtrConstant(MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset())));
4670  return WordNotEqual(WordAnd(flags, IntPtrConstant(mask)),
4671  IntPtrConstant(0));
4672  }
4673 
4674  TNode<BoolT> IsPageFlagReset(TNode<IntPtrT> object, int mask) {
4675  TNode<IntPtrT> header = MemoryChunkFromAddress(object);
4676  TNode<IntPtrT> flags = UncheckedCast<IntPtrT>(
4677  Load(MachineType::Pointer(), header,
4678  IntPtrConstant(MemoryChunk::FlagsOffset())));
4679  return WordEqual(WordAnd(flags, IntPtrConstant(mask)), IntPtrConstant(0));
4680  }

4857 class V8_EXPORT_PRIVATE CodeStubArguments {
4858  public:
4859  // |argc| specifies the number of arguments passed to the builtin.
4860  CodeStubArguments(CodeStubAssembler* assembler, TNode<IntPtrT> argc)
4861  : CodeStubArguments(assembler, argc, TNode<RawPtrT>()) {}

4865  TNode<RawPtrT> fp);
4866 
4867  // Used by Torque to construct arguments based on a Torque-defined
4868  // struct of values.
4869  CodeStubArguments(CodeStubAssembler* assembler,
4870  TorqueStructArguments torque_arguments)
4871  : assembler_(assembler),
4872  argc_(torque_arguments.actual_count),
4873  base_(torque_arguments.base),
4874  fp_(torque_arguments.frame) {}
4875 
4876  // Return true if there may be additional padding arguments, false otherwise.
4877  bool MayHavePaddingArguments() const;
4878 
4879  TNode<JSAny> GetReceiver() const;
4880  // Replaces receiver argument on the expression stack. Should be used only
4881  // for manipulating arguments in trampoline builtins before tail calling
4882  // further with passing all the JS arguments as is.
4883  void SetReceiver(TNode<JSAny> object) const;
4884 
4885  // Computes address of the index'th argument.
4886  TNode<RawPtrT> AtIndexPtr(TNode<IntPtrT> index) const;
4887 
4888  // |index| is zero-based and does not include the receiver
4889  TNode<JSAny> AtIndex(TNode<IntPtrT> index) const;
4890  TNode<JSAny> AtIndex(int index) const;
4891 
4892  // Return the number of arguments (excluding the receiver).
4893  TNode<IntPtrT> GetLengthWithoutReceiver() const;
4894  // Return the number of arguments (including the receiver).
4895  TNode<IntPtrT> GetLengthWithReceiver() const;
4896 
4897  TorqueStructArguments GetTorqueArguments() const {
4898  return TorqueStructArguments{fp_, base_, GetLengthWithoutReceiver(), argc_};
4899  }
4900 
4901  TNode<JSAny> GetOptionalArgumentValue(TNode<IntPtrT> index,
4902  TNode<JSAny> default_value);
4903  TNode<JSAny> GetOptionalArgumentValue(TNode<IntPtrT> index) {
4904  return GetOptionalArgumentValue(index, assembler_->UndefinedConstant());
4905  }
4906  TNode<JSAny> GetOptionalArgumentValue(int index) {
4907  return GetOptionalArgumentValue(assembler_->IntPtrConstant(index));
4908  }
4909 
4910  // Iteration doesn't include the receiver. |first| and |last| are zero-based.
4911  using ForEachBodyFunction = std::function<void(TNode<JSAny> arg)>;
4912  void ForEach(const ForEachBodyFunction& body, TNode<IntPtrT> first = {},
4913  TNode<IntPtrT> last = {}) const {
4914  CodeStubAssembler::VariableList list(0, assembler_->zone());

4916  }
4917  void ForEach(const CodeStubAssembler::VariableList& vars,
4918  const ForEachBodyFunction& body, TNode<IntPtrT> first = {},
4919  TNode<IntPtrT> last = {}) const;
4920 
4921  void PopAndReturn(TNode<JSAny> value);
4922 
4923  private:
4924  CodeStubAssembler* assembler_;
4925  TNode<IntPtrT> argc_;
4926  TNode<RawPtrT> base_;
4927  TNode<RawPtrT> fp_;

4930 class ToDirectStringAssembler : public CodeStubAssembler {
4931  private:
4932  enum StringPointerKind { PTR_TO_DATA, PTR_TO_STRING };
4933 
4934  public:
4935  enum Flag {
4936  kDontUnpackSlicedStrings = 1 << 0,
4937  };
4938  using Flags = base::Flags<Flag>;
4939 
4940  ToDirectStringAssembler(compiler::CodeAssemblerState* state,
4941  TNode<String> string, Flags flags = Flags());
4942 
4943  // Converts flat cons, thin, and sliced strings and returns the direct
4944  // string. The result can be either a sequential or external string.
4945  // Jumps to if_bailout if the string if the string is indirect and cannot
4946  // be unpacked.
4947  TNode<String> TryToDirect(Label* if_bailout);
4948 
4949  // As above, but flattens in runtime if the string cannot be unpacked
4950  // otherwise.
4951  TNode<String> ToDirect();
4952 
4953  // Returns a pointer to the beginning of the string data.
4954  // Jumps to if_bailout if the external string cannot be unpacked.
4955  TNode<RawPtrT> PointerToData(Label* if_bailout) {
4956  return TryToSequential(PTR_TO_DATA, if_bailout);
4957  }
4958 
4959  // Returns a pointer that, offset-wise, looks like a String.
4960  // Jumps to if_bailout if the external string cannot be unpacked.
4961  TNode<RawPtrT> PointerToString(Label* if_bailout) {
4962  return TryToSequential(PTR_TO_STRING, if_bailout);
4963  }
4964 
4965  TNode<BoolT> IsOneByte();
4966 
4967  TNode<String> string() { return var_string_.value(); }
4968  TNode<IntPtrT> offset() { return var_offset_.value(); }
4969  TNode<Word32T> is_external() { return var_is_external_.value(); }
4970 
4971  private:
4972  TNode<RawPtrT> TryToSequential(StringPointerKind ptr_kind, Label* if_bailout);
4973 
4974  TVariable<String> var_string_;
4975 #if V8_STATIC_ROOTS_BOOL
4976  TVariable<Map> var_map_;
4977 #else
4978  TVariable<Int32T> var_instance_type_;
4979 #endif
4980  // TODO(v8:9880): Use UintPtrT here.
4981  TVariable<IntPtrT> var_offset_;
4982  TVariable<Word32T> var_is_external_;
4983 
4984  const Flags flags_;
4985 };
